            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Handling Corporation Taxes</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">Once you successfully finish your <strong>company registration</strong>, your entity is a separate legal person. Unlike branches or sole traders, a UK Limited Company will <strong>pay corporation tax</strong> only on its UK-derived or globally subjected corporate profits. We help you <strong>register for corporation tax</strong> as part of our premium compliance support.</p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Legal Requirements for Non-Residents</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">To **open company in uk non resident** founders must satisfy a few basic **legal requirements**: a unique company name, at least one director (no **uk resident directors** required), and a **registered office address** within the UK jurisdiction. Every **person with significant control** must also be declared to ensure transparency.</p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Start Setting Up a UK Company</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">The process is lightning fast. You don't need a visa, you don't need to visit London, and you don't need to wait weeks. Our authorized agents provide the expertise you need to **form a uk company** and scale your **uk based** business globally.</p>
